IN RE: INVESTIGATION OF A . C. FRANKS, Attorney 14 So. (2nd) 672

June Term, 1943

July 24, 1943 En Banc Rehearing Denied Sept. 20, 1943 F. M. Hudson and H. H. Eyles, for appellant. Grady C. Harris, for appellee. *337PER CURIAM:

Upon consideration of the record and the arguments of counsel, our conclusion is that the first paragraph of the court’s order of January 13, 1943, should be affirmed and the second paragraph reversed.

It is so ordered.

BUFORD, C. J., TERRELL, CHAPMAN, THOMAS, ADAMS and SEBRING, JJ., concur.
